; Source: Computer Science Logo Style, Volume 2 Chapter 7 Pattern Matcher
; and Chapter 9 Doctor.
; Source URLs:
; - https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~bh/v2ch7/match.html
; - https://people.eecs.berkeley.edu/~bh/v2ch9/doctor.html
; Modeled deterministic fixture: drives a tiny Doctor-style responder with
; scripted multi-turn input and stable transcript normalization.

to doctor.demo
print [Doctor is listening.]
catch "done [forever [doctor.turn]]
end

to doctor.turn
local "line
make "line readlist
if equalp :line [bye] [print [Goodbye.] throw "done "bye]
print respond :line
end

to respond :line
if equalp :line [hello] [output [How do you do?]]
if and equalp first :line "i equalp first butfirst :line "need ~
   [output sentence [Why do you need] sentence butfirst butfirst :line [?]]
if and equalp first :line "i equalp first butfirst :line "feel ~
   [output sentence [Do you often feel] sentence butfirst butfirst :line [?]]
output [Please go on.]
end

doctor.demo
